'''Adam Masina''' (born 2 January 1994) is a Moroccan-born Italian professional [[association football|footballer]] who currently plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].
== Club career == Masina was born in [[Khouribga]], Morocco. He returned to [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]] in 2013 after a successful loan in [[A.C. Giacomense|Giacomense]] and made his Bologna debut in a 2–1 away win over [[U.S. Latina Calcio|Latina]] on 12 October 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/match/latina-vs-bologna/1882279/lineups|publisher=goal.com|title=Latina 1–2 Bologna|date=12 October 2014}}</ref> He helped the club obtain [[Serie A]] promotion, later making his debut in the top division, and scoring his first goal in Serie A in an injury time victory at [[Carpi F.C. 1909|Carpi]].<ref name="Un 2015 da favola per Masina">{{cite web|url=http://it.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=2321616.html|title=Un 2015 da favola per Masina|publisher=UEFA.com|date=29 December 2015|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref>
== International career == In November 2015 [[Luigi Di Biagio]] called Masina to represent [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U21 team]] after obtaining FIFA transfer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/2530263/2015/11/News.shtml|title=Arrivato il transfert dalla FIFA: Di Biagio convoca il difensore del Bologna Masina|trans-title=FIFA transfer has arrived: Di Biagio calls up Bologna defender Masina|publisher=FIGC|language=Italian|date=10 November 2015|accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref> He made his debut with the Italy U21 side on 17 November 2015, in a [[2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|Euro 2017 qualification]] match against [[Lithuania national under-21 football team|Lithuania]].<ref name="Un 2015 da favola per Masina"/>
== Style of play == Masina is known in particular for his technique, pace and energy as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]].<ref name="Un 2015 da favola per Masina"/>
== Honours == === Individual === *[[Serie B Footballer of the Year]]: 2015<ref name="Oscar del Calcio, dominio Juve">{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/14-12-2015/juventus-buffon-elogia-donnarumma-ha-doti-gia-grande-1301295361892.shtml|title=Oscar del Calcio, dominio Juve. Buffon: "Donnarumma ha doti da grande"|trans-title=Serie A Oscars, Juve dominate. Buffon: "Donnarumma has the characteristics to be great"|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|date=14 December 2015|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>
